Chelsea, Real Madrid Complete Quarterfinal Field in Champions League

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-03-16T21:38:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/chelsea-real-madrid-complete-quarterfinal-field-in-champions-league.html
Real  Madrid  beat Lyon 3-0 to reach
the quarterfinals of soccer’s Champions League, while Chelsea
advanced with a 0-0 tie against Copenhagen.  Marcelo, Karim Benzema and Angel di Maria scored at the
Bernabeu Stadium in Madrid as Real completed a 4-1 victory over
two games. Chelsea’s scoreless home draw was enough to send it
through after winning the opening match in Copenhagen 2-0.  The two joined defending champion Inter Milan, Barcelona,
Schalke,  Shakhtar Donetsk , Manchester United and Tottenahm in
the final eight of Europe’s top club competition. The draw for
the quarterfinal and semifinal rounds will be held in two days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  